#!/usr/bin/env bash
cat <<'EOF'
bin/xdebug has been removed.

Xdebug now runs in a dedicated phpfpm-xdebug container. Nginx routes
requests to it when the XDEBUG_SESSION cookie is set; all other
requests hit the main phpfpm container, which no longer loads the
extension at all. Nothing to toggle.

Existing projects: run `bin/setup-nginx` once to update nginx.conf
so cookie-triggered routing works (new projects get this automatically).

CLI:
  bin/debug-cli <command>    # runs in phpfpm-xdebug
  bin/cli <command>          # runs in phpfpm

See README -> Xdebug for IDE setup.
EOF
exit 1
